	<pb facs="liv_001098_0001" n="0001"/><!-- Change both @facs and @n -->
	<!-- Start each page with a <pb> formatted as above -->

<!-- If this is a letter or similar with an opener (with content such as dateline and/or salute) add it. For example: -->

<lb/><opener><dateline rend="right"><placeName>Burnbank<add place="marginleft">194</add>
<lb/>Hamilton</placeName> 
<lb/><date when="1857-09-21">Monday 21st
<lb/><add place="inspace" hand="#U" rend="gray">[Sept. 1857]</add></date></dateline><!--Addition below dateline, written in unknown hand. Did I code this correctly? EC --><!-- Since it's in the space where a blank line would have been, I've put place='inspace'. AW -->
<lb/>    
<lb/><salute>My Dear Friend</salute></opener><!-- Change line info as appropriate -->
<lb/><p>I got your
<lb/>note a minute
<lb/>ago just when
<lb/>on the point of 
<lb/>startng for
<lb/><placeName><settlement type="city">Edinburgh</settlement></placeName> on
<lb/>Thursday we are
<lb/>at <placeName><settlement type="city">Dundee</settlement></placeName>

	<pb facs="liv_001098_0002" n="0002"/>
<lb/>Saturday <placeName><settlement type="cit">Kendal</settlement></placeName> on 
<lb/>our way to 
<lb/><placeName><settlement type="city">Liverpool</settlement></placeName> &amp; <placeName><settlement type="city">Leeds</settlement></placeName>
<lb/>if my mother's 
<lb/>illness does not
<lb/>become serious
<lb/>I asked every
<lb/>body for the <term type="occupation">D<hi rend="sup">r</hi></term>
<lb/>the Presbytery
<lb/>sir <persName>James Anderson</persName>
<lb/>but no <term type="occupation">doctor</term>
<lb/>to be seen &amp; now

	<pb facs="liv_001098_0003" n="0003"/>
<lb/>I fear I am off
<lb/>before seeing you 
<lb/><placeName><settlement><unclear cert="low">Lionoying</unclear></settlement></placeName><!---Not sure exactly what city this is--><!-- Not even clear that it's a city! AW --> very
<lb/>disagreeable I assure
<lb/>you &amp; very glad
<lb/>I shall be to bid <!--Blot on page obscures word--><!-- Fixed. AW -->
<lb/>adeu to it for
<lb/>ever <persName>M<hi rend="sup underline">rs</hi> L.</persName>
<lb/>follows me <w>to- 
<lb break="no"/>morrow</w> - part
<lb/>with the <term type="nationality">Canadian</term>
<lb/>brother today - he 
<lb/>goes to <placeName><settlement type="city">Liverpool</settlement></placeName>
<lb/>to sail thence

	<pb facs="liv_001098_0004" n="0004"/>
<lb/><persName>M<hi rend="sup underline">rs</hi> <choice><abbr>L.</abbr><expan>Livingstone</expan></choice></persName> joins in
<lb/>kindest salutations
<lb/>to yourself and
<lb/>to <persName><term type="occupation">D<hi rend="sup">r</hi></term></persName><!--talking about specific person here, not sure who. EC--><!-- Impossible to know since we don't know the recipient. AW -->
</p>

<!-- If there is a letter or similar with a closer with content such as salute or signed -->
<lb/><closer><salute>I am
<lb/>affectionately yours,</salute><!-- Change as appropriate -->
<lb/><signed><persName>David Livingstone</persName></signed></closer>
            
<lb/><postscript><p>P.S.if I do come back
<lb/>I shall let you
<lb/>know</p></postscript><!--Won't validate because of postscript, can someone else take a look. EC--><!-- The text in a postscript needs to also be inside of a <p> (or <ab>, though <p> seems more logical). AW -->



